    "body": "> But it's not just an implementation detail. It shows through in the language. Having such arbitrary limits on scientific notation, but not normal literals is at least a wart on the language, if not an outright bug.\r\n\r\nIt's non-existent cases that will *never* happen in practice. We put up those limits to get fuzzers to shut up - there is zero cause for spending time on doing this more properly.",
