    "body": "Nowhere in the code, in the error messages or elsewhere it says that we enforce a strict proper limit of 4096 bits on anything.\r\nThis is *not* worth keeping an issue open just as well as it wasn't worth spending time on doing this more properly when we added this - this discussion is already an unnecessary distraction as it stands.\r\nWe won't fix this. Sooner than fixing this directly, we'll change the way literals are handled and our bigint backend in general. Please stop these unnecessary arguments ;-).",
